.IX Title "cgGetArraySize 3"
.TH cgGetArraySize 3 "Cg Toolkit 3.0" "perl v5.10.0" "Cg Core Runtime API"
.if n .ad l
.nh
.SH "NAME"
\&\fBcgGetArraySize\fR \- get the size of one dimension of an array parameter
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.IX Header "SYNOPSIS"
.Vb 1
\&  #include <Cg/cg.h>
\&
\&  int cgGetArraySize( CGparameter param,
\&                      int dimension );
.Ve
.SH "PARAMETERS"
.IX Header "PARAMETERS"
.IP "param" 8
.IX Item "param"
The array parameter handle.
.IP "dimension" 8
.IX Item "dimension"
The array dimension whose size will be returned.
.SH "RETURN VALUES"
.IX Header "RETURN VALUES"
Returns the size of \fBparam\fR if \fBparam\fR is an array.
.PP
Returns \fB0\fR if \fBparam\fR is not an array, or an error occurs.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.IX Header "DESCRIPTION"
\&\fBcgGetArraySize\fR returns the size of the given dimension
of the array specified by \fBparam\fR.  \fBcgGetArraySize\fR is used when
inspecting an array parameter in a program.
.SH "EXAMPLES"
.IX Header "EXAMPLES"
.Vb 9
\&  /* Compute the number of elements in an array, in the */
\&  /* style of cgGetArrayTotalSize(param) */
\&  int elements = cgGetArraySize(param, 0);
\&  if (elements>0) {
\&    int dim = cgGetArrayDimension(param);
\&    for (int i = 1; i < dim; i++) {
\&       elements *= cgGetArraySize(param, i);
\&    }
\&  }
.Ve
.SH "ERRORS"
.IX Header "ERRORS"
\&\fB\s-1CG_INVALID_DIMENSION_ERROR\s0\fR is generated if \fBdimension\fR is less than 0.
.PP
\&\fB\s-1CG_INVALID_PARAM_HANDLE_ERROR\s0\fR is generated if \fBparam\fR is not a valid parameter.
.SH "HISTORY"
.IX Header "HISTORY"
\&\fBcgGetArraySize\fR was introduced in Cg 1.1.
